explanation: This solution uses a recursive approach to solve the problem. It takes advantage of the fact that the number of operations required to transform n into 0 is equal to the number of 1s in the binary representation of n. The recursive function calculates the number of 1s by shifting the bits of n to the right and counting the number of 1s in the resulting binary representation. The base case for the recursion is when n is 0, in which case the number of operations is 0. The time complexity of this solution is O(log n) because each recursive call shifts the bits of n to the right, effectively dividing the number of bits in n by 2. The space complexity is also O(log n) because the maximum depth of the recursion tree is equal to the number of bits in n.

